# ── Google Sheets CSV URL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All data (wards and special events) lives in a single published Google Sheet tab.
#
# Sheet columns (row 1 must be a header row with these exact names):
#   type, key, name, displayTime, windowStart, windowEnd, url, date
#
# Use type="ward" for ward rows and type="event" for special event rows.
# Leave inapplicable columns blank (e.g. ward rows have no date; event rows have no key).
#
# How to publish:
#   1. Open your Google Sheet
#   2. File → Share → Publish to web
#   3. Under "Link", select the sheet tab and choose "Comma-separated values (.csv)"
#   4. Click Publish and copy the URL
#
# The URL will look like:
#   https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SHEET_ID/pub?gid=0&single=true&output=csv
#
# Leave blank to use the placeholder ward data defined in src/lib/data.js
SHEET_CSV_URL=
